        <h3>Lifestyle activism is pretty much a scam.</h3>
        <p>In case you weren't aware, the idea of the "Personal Carbon Footprint" is {% ext "https://mashable.com/feature/carbon-footprint-pr-campaign-sham" %}Big Oil propaganda{% endext %} meant to shift the blame off super-polluting corporations and on to you and me.</p>
    {% endslide %}
    {% slide %}
        <p>Now <em>of course</em> there are things we can do in our own lives that will reduce the amount of carbon emitted by people - mostly {% ext "https://www.lunduniversity.lu.se/article/four-lifestyle-choices-most-reduce-your-carbon-footprint" %}avoiding flying, driving, and eating meat{% endext %}.</p>
    {% endslide %}
    {% slide %}
        <p>But the biggest impact we can have is to make systemic changes, using {% ext "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_movement#Activities" %}collective{% endext %}, {% ext "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax" %}economic{% endext %}, {% ext "https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/On-Fire/Naomi-Klein/9781982129910" %}political{% endext %}, and {% ext "https://www.unep.org/news-and-stories/story/battle-against-climate-change-courts-become-new-frontier" %}legal{% endext %} actions.</p>
    {% endslide %}
    {% slide %}
