        <h3>Streaming video</h3>
        <figure>
        {% image "images/Ampex-avr3.jpeg", "Ampex AVR-3 Quad VTR video system", "(min-width: 30em) 600px, 100vw", "J. Thurion The original uploader was Belgavox at French Wikipedia., CC BY-SA 3.0 <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/>, via Wikimedia Commons" %}
        </figure>
        <p>Actually some good news here: I had assumed that streaming media would be really gnarly for the environment, having read some scary articles a few years back. Turns out, {% ext "https://www.iea.org/commentaries/the-carbon-footprint-of-streaming-video-fact-checking-the-headlines#:~:text=Calculate%20your%20emissions" %}watching one hour of Netflix on a big TV in 4K{% endext %} has the same carbon footprint as <span data-annotate data-ann-color="var(--warning)" data-ann-type="underline">boiling a kettle twice</span>. Not too bad! And those numbers can be improved drastically by using a smaller device, and streaming in lower quality.</p>
        <figure>
        {% image "images/calculate-your-emissions.png", "ALT", "(min-width: 30em) 600px, 100vw", "George Kamiya, IEA" %}
            <figcaption>Cool interactive graphs via the {% ext "https://www.iea.org/commentaries/the-carbon-footprint-of-streaming-video-fact-checking-the-headlines#:~:text=Calculate%20your%20emissions" %}International Energy Agency{% endext %}</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>In part, this is thanks to the {% ext "https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3226029" %}impressive efficiency gains in data centres{% endext %} that have been happening for the last decade.</p>
    {% endslide %}
    {% slide %}
        <h3>Remote work</h3>
        <figure>
            {% image "images/video-phone.jpg", "Video telephony as imagined in the year 2000, as imagined in 1910. From a French card.", "(min-width: 30em) 600px, 100vw", "Villemard, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" %}
            <figcaption>Video telephony as imagined in the year 2000, as imagined in 1910. From a French card.</figcaption>
