            <figcaption>I've heard that L. Frank Baum's 'Oz' books were a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Political_interpretations_of_The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz#Monetary_policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">satire of late 19th-century monetary policy<span class="show-for-sr"> Opens in a new window</span></a>, but honestly I felt like I needed something to break up this absurd technical nonsense, and I really love Ozma's vibe&nbsp;here.</figcaption>
