        <blockquote>
            If youâ€™re on the plane, youâ€™re obviously responsible for a portion of its emissions. But if you hadnâ€™t bought the ticket, the plane probably would have taken off with other passengers and polluted the same amount anywayâ€¦ If enough people decide to start flying who werenâ€™t planning to before, an airline might decide to operate more flights â€” which means more emissions overall.
            <footer><cite>{% ext "https://www.theverge.com/2021/3/15/22328203/nft-cryptoart-ethereum-blockchain-climate-change#:~:text=If%20you%E2%80%99re%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20obviously%20responsible%20for%20a%20portion%20of%20its%20emissions." %}- The Verge{% endext %}</cite></footer>
        </blockquote>
        <p>So where is this headed? Ugh, who knows. A significant chunk of the NFT market moved from Ethereum to {% ext "https://www.coindesk.com/business/2022/01/19/jpmorgan-says-ethereum-is-losing-nft-market-share-to-solana/" %}proof-of-stake driven competitor Solana{% endext %} at the beginning of the year, but then {% ext "https://www.cnbc.com/2022/06/01/solana-suffered-its-second-outage-in-a-month-sending-price-plunging.html" %}Solana has had a bunch of outages this year{% endext %}, and <span data-annotate data-ann-type="underline" data-ann-color="var(--warning)">maybe Ethereum will finally switch to PoS</span> and reduce their energy consumption by 99.99%, as {% ext "https://www.nbcnews.com/news/rcna1030#:~:text=Researchers%20like%20Ryan%20believe%20that%20the%20result%20is%20that%20energy%20consumption%20for%20proof%20of%20stake%20is%2099.99%20percent%20lower%20than%20proof%20of%20work." %}claimed by Danny Ryan{% endext %}, a researcher for the Ethereum Foundation. Unfortunately, <span data-annotate data-ann-type="underline" data-ann-color="var(--warning)">there are {% ext "https://cointelegraph.com/news/eager-to-work-bitcoin-switch-to-proof-of-stake-remains-unlikely" %}no such plans for Bitcoin{% endext %}</span>, and <span data-annotate data-ann-type="underline" data-ann-color="var(--warning)">who <em>knows</em> what the plan is for the cash being {% ext "https://fortune.com/2022/02/08/venture-capital-firms-are-shoveling-cash-at-companies-building-web3-heres-what-comes-next/" %}"shoveled" at Web3 companies{% endext %}</span> by venture capital firms.</p>
